# Quick Cheat Sheet

| Expression | Meaning |
|------------|----------|
| root | Reference to root node |
| root.val | Value stored in root |
| root.left | Left child reference |
| root.right | Right child reference |
| root.left.val | Value of left child |
| root.right.val | Value of right child |
| root.left.left | Left child's left child |
| root.left.right | Left child's right child |
| root.left.right.val | Value of left-right node |

---

# Golden Rule

> Think of the dot (`.`) operator as:
>
> **"Go inside this object and access something."**

Examples:

```java
root.val
```

→ Go inside root and get value.

```java
root.left
```

→ Go inside root and get left reference.

```java
root.left.right
```

→ Go to left child, then go to its right child.

```java
root.left.right.val
```

→ Finally read the value stored in that node.



